## Business Logic

### Summary of the Event Management System

The Event Management System is designed to facilitate the management of events, bookings, vendors, and venues through a user-friendly interface. Users can register, log in, and manage their profiles and bookings. The system allows for the creation and submission of events, which are initially set to a "pending" status. Users can view their booking history and manage new bookings, while vendors can be assigned to events based on specific criteria. Venue management ensures that all necessary details are captured before an event can be scheduled. The system operates under defined business rules, such as password security and event status management, ensuring a reliable and efficient experience for all stakeholders involved.

### API Overview

| Base Path                     | Source Repository                          | Description                                                                                             |
|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `/register`                   | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for registering a new user in the system.                                                           |
| `/login`                      | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for authenticating users to access their accounts.                                                  |
| `/events`                     | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for retrieving a list of all events available in the system.                                       |
| `/eventForm`                  | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for displaying the event creation form to users.                                                   |
| `/submit`                     | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for submitting a new event created by the user.                                                    |
| `/bookings`                   | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for retrieving all bookings made by the user.                                                      |
| `/vendors`                    | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for retrieving a list of all available vendors in the system.                                      |
| `/addvenue`                   | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for adding a new venue to the system.                                                               |
| `/VenueList`                  | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for viewing the list of all venues registered in the system.                                       |
| `/assignVendor/{bookingId}`   | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for assigning a vendor to a specific booking.                                                       |
| `/history`                    | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for viewing the booking history of the user.                                                       |
| `/newbooking`                 | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for viewing new bookings that are yet to be processed.                                             |
| `/newbooking/newView/{id}`    | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for viewing detailed information about a specific booking.                                         |
| `/updateProfile`              | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for updating the userâ€™s profile information.                                                       |
| `/confirmation`               | [GitHub Repo Link](#)                    | API for displaying confirmation of event registration after submission.                                 |

### Overall API Specification

| Endpoint                      | Method | Authentication | Description                               | Expected Response                   |
|-------------------------------|--------|----------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| `/register`                   | POST   | No             | Register a new user                       | Redirect to `/login`               |
| `/login`                      | POST   | No             | Authenticate user                         | Redirect to `/events` or `/login`  |
| `/events`                     | GET    | Yes            | Get all events                           | List of events                      |
| `/eventForm`                  | GET    | Yes            | Show event creation form                 | Event creation form view            |
| `/submit`                     | POST   | Yes            | Submit a new event                       | Redirect to `/confirmation`        |
| `/bookings`                   | GET    | Yes            | Get all bookings                         | List of bookings                    |
| `/vendors`                    | GET    | Yes            | Get all vendors                          | List of vendors                     |
| `/addvenue`                   | POST   | Yes            | Add a new venue                          | Redirect to `/index`               |
| `/VenueList`                  | GET    | Yes            | View list of venues                      | List of venues                      |
| `/assignVendor/{bookingId}`   | POST   | Yes            | Assign a vendor to a booking             | Success or failure message          |
| `/history`                    | GET    | Yes            | View booking history                     | List of booking history             |
| `/newbooking`                 | GET    | Yes            | View new bookings                        | List of new bookings                |
| `/newbooking/newView/{id}`   | GET    | Yes            | View details of a specific booking       | Booking details view                |
| `/updateProfile`              | POST   | Yes            | Update user profile                      | Redirect based on success/failure   |
| `/confirmation`               | GET    | Yes            | Show confirmation of event registration   | Confirmation view                   |

This structured overview provides a comprehensive understanding of the Event Management System's functionalities, API endpoints, and their respective purposes. If you require further details or clarifications, please let me know!

## Plant UML script

Here is a PlantUML sequence diagram script that captures the key interactions and processes of the Event Management System as described in your business logic. This script includes all the main actors, interactions, decision points, and relevant components.

```plantuml
@startuml
actor User
actor Vendor
actor Administrator
participant "CustomerController" as CC
participant "EventController" as EC
participant "BookingController" as BC
participant "VendorController" as VC
participant "VenueListController" as VLC
participant "CustomerRepository" as CR
participant "EventRepository" as ER
participant "BookingService" as BS
participant "VenueListService" as VLS
participant "KafkaPublisher" as KP
participant "RabbitMqPublisher" as RP

User -> CC: POST /register(username, password, email)
CC -> CR: saveUser(user)
CR -> CC: success
CC -> User: Redirect to /login

User -> CC: POST /login(username, password)
CC -> CR: authenticateUser(username, hashedPassword)
CR -> CC: authenticationResult
alt successful login
    CC -> User: Redirect to /events
else failed login
    CC -> User: Redirect to /login
end

User -> EC: GET /events
EC -> ER: getAllEvents()
ER -> EC: listOfEvents
EC -> User: Display events

User -> EC: GET /eventForm
EC -> User: Show event creation form

User -> EC: POST /submit(eventDetails)
EC -> ER: saveEvent(event)
ER -> EC: eventSaved
EC -> User: Redirect to /confirmation

User -> BC: GET /bookings
BC -> ER: getAllBookings()
ER -> BC: listOfBookings
BC -> User: Display bookings

User -> VC: GET /vendors
VC -> ER: getAllVendors()
ER -> VC: listOfVendors
VC -> User: Display vendors

User -> VLC: POST /addvenue(venueDetails)
VLC -> VLS: saveVenue(venue)
VLS -> VLC: venueSaved
VLC -> User: Redirect to /index

User -> VLC: GET /VenueList
VLC -> VLS: getAllVenues()
VLS -> VLC: listOfVenues
VLC -> User: Display venues

User -> VC: POST /assignVendor/{bookingId}(vendorId)
VC -> BS: assignVendorToBooking(bookingId, vendorId)
BS -> VC: assignmentResult
VC -> User: Success or failure message

User -> BC: GET /history
BC -> ER: getBookingHistory()
ER -> BC: listOfBookingHistory
BC -> User: Display booking history

User -> BC: GET /newbooking
BC -> ER: getNewBookings()
ER -> BC: listOfNewBookings
BC -> User: Display new bookings

User -> BC: GET /newbooking/newView/{id}
BC -> ER: getBookingDetails(id)
ER -> BC: bookingDetails
BC -> User: Display booking details

User -> CC: POST /updateProfile(userDetails)
CC -> CR: updateUserProfile(userDetails)
CR -> CC: updateResult
CC -> User: Redirect based on success/failure

User -> CC: GET /confirmation
CC -> User: Show confirmation of event registration

note right of KP: Kafka is used for\nevent processing and notifications.
note right of RP: RabbitMQ is used for\nasynchronous communication.

@enduml
```

### Explanation of the Diagram
1. **Actors and Participants**: The diagram includes all main actors (User, Vendor, Administrator) and relevant components (CustomerController, EventController, etc.).
2. **Interactions**: Each interaction follows the specified endpoints, showing the flow of requests and responses between the user and system components.
3. **Decision Points**: The script captures critical decision points like user authentication and event submission status.
4. **Clear Messages**: Each interaction is described clearly to represent the action being taken.
5. **Components**: All components involved in the service are mentioned, including repositories and services.
6. **Message Queue**: Notes are included to indicate the use of Kafka and RabbitMQ for asynchronous communication.

# API Documentation

## /register POST
Endpoint URL: `/register`  
HTTP Method: POST  
Authentication: None  
Authorization: None  
Description: Register a new user  

### Request Parameters
| Parameter Name | Type   | Required | Description                      |
|----------------|--------|----------|----------------------------------|
| username       | string | Yes      | Unique username for the user     |
| password       | string | Yes      | Password for the user            |
| email          | string | Yes      | User's email address             |
| address        | string | No       | User's address                   |
| mobile         | string | No       | User's mobile number             |

### Sample Request
```json
{
  "username": "john_doe",
  "password": "securepassword123",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "address": "123 Main St",
  "mobile": "1234567890"
}
```

### Response Parameters
| Field Name | Type   | Description                       |
|------------|--------|-----------------------------------|
| message     | string | Confirmation message of registration |
| userId      | int    | ID of the newly created user      |

### Sample Response
```json
{
  "message": "Registration successful.",
  "userId": 1
}
```

### Components Involved
- `CustomerController`
- `CustomerRepository`

### Data Mapping
| Source Field   | Target Field         | Transformation        |
|----------------|----------------------|------------------------|
| request.username | db_record.username   | Direct mapping         |
| request.password | db_record.password   | Hashing before storage |
| request.email    | db_record.email      | Direct mapping         |

### Sample Errors
```json
{
  "error": "User already exists.",
  "code": 400,
  "message": "A user with this username already exists."
}
```

### Root Exception Details
| Name               | Description                  | Header/Payload | Type   | Mandatory/Optional | Notes                       |
|--------------------|-----------------------------|----------------|--------|---------------------|-----------------------------|
| UserAlreadyExists   | User registration conflict   | Payload        | string | Mandatory           | Username must be unique     |

### Error Codes
| HTTP Code | Message                     | Description                                 |
|-----------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| 400       | User already exists         | A user with this username already exists.  |
| 500       | Internal Server Error       | An unexpected error occurred.               |

## /history GET
Endpoint URL: `/history`  
HTTP Method: GET  
Authentication: Bearer Token Required  
Authorization: None  
Description: View booking history  

### Request Parameters
| Parameter Name | Type   | Required | Description                      |
|----------------|--------|----------|----------------------------------|
| None           | -      | -        | No parameters required           |

### Sample Request
```http
GET /history HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer abc123xyz456
```

### Response Parameters
| Field Name | Type   | Description                       |
|------------|--------|-----------------------------------|
| history     | array  | List of booking history           |

### Sample Response
```json
{
  "history": [
    {
      "bookingId": 1,
      "eventId": 1,
      "status": "accepted",
      "date": "2023-12-01"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Components Involved
- `BookingController`
- `EventRepository`

### Data Mapping
| Source Field   | Target Field         | Transformation        |
|----------------|----------------------|------------------------|
| db_record.history | response.history    | Direct mapping         |

### Sample Errors
```json
{
  "error": "Unauthorized access.",
  "code": 401,
  "message": "Token is missing or invalid."
}
```

### Root Exception Details
| Name               | Description                  | Header/Payload | Type   | Mandatory/Optional | Notes                       |
|--------------------|-----------------------------|----------------|--------|---------------------|-----------------------------|
| UnauthorizedAccess  | Access denied due to invalid token | Header         | string | Mandatory           | Token must be valid        |

### Error Codes
| HTTP Code | Message                     | Description                                 |
|-----------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| 401       | Unauthorized access         | Token is missing or invalid.                |
| 500       | Internal Server Error       | An unexpected error occurred.               |

Authorization: Bearer abc123xyz456

### Response Parameters

## /updateProfile POST
Endpoint URL: `/updateProfile`  
HTTP Method: POST  
Authentication: Bearer Token Required  
Authorization: None  
Description: Update user profile  

### Request Parameters
| Parameter Name | Type   | Required | Description                      |
|----------------|--------|----------|----------------------------------|
| username       | string | Yes      | New username for the user        |
| email          | string | Yes      | New email address for the user   |
| address        | string | No       | New address for the user         |
| mobile         | string | No       | New mobile number for the user   |

### Sample Request
```json
{
  "username": "john_doe_updated",
  "email": "john_updated@example.com",
  "address": "789 Pine St",
  "mobile": "9876543210"
}
```

### Response Parameters
| Field Name | Type   | Description                       |
|------------|--------|-----------------------------------|
| message     | string | Confirmation message of profile update |

### Sample Response
```json
{
  "message": "Profile updated successfully."
}
```

### Components Involved
- `CustomerController`
- `CustomerRepository`

### Data Mapping
| Source Field   | Target Field         | Transformation        |
|----------------|----------------------|------------------------|
| request.username | db_record.username   | Direct mapping         |
| request.email    | db_record.email      | Direct mapping         |

### Sample Errors
```json
{
  "error": "Update failed.",
  "code": 400,
  "message": "Profile details are incomplete."
}
```

### Root Exception Details
| Name               | Description                  | Header/Payload | Type   | Mandatory/Optional | Notes                       |
|--------------------|-----------------------------|----------------|--------|---------------------|-----------------------------|
| UpdateFailed        | Profile update failure       | Payload        | string | Mandatory           | All required fields must be provided |

### Error Codes
| HTTP Code | Message                     | Description                                 |
|-----------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
| 400       | Update failed               | Profile details are incomplete.             |
| 500       | Internal Server Error       | An unexpected error occurred.               |
